42:06.000 --> 42:08.000
and activists.

42:08.000 --> 42:10.000
For example,

42:10.000 --> 42:12.000
the Qing Dynasty

42:12.000 --> 42:14.000
was an empire

42:14.000 --> 42:16.000
with Han people,

42:16.000 --> 42:18.000
Tibetans,

42:18.000 --> 42:20.000
Mongols,

42:20.000 --> 42:22.000
ethnic minorities

42:22.000 --> 42:24.000
and Xinjiang people.

42:24.000 --> 42:26.000
The next question is

42:26.000 --> 42:28.000
that we all know that

42:28.000 --> 42:30.000
there is a law called the Qing Dynasty Law.

42:30.000 --> 42:32.000
But did the Qing Dynasty Law

42:32.000 --> 42:34.000
apply in Tibet?

42:34.000 --> 42:36.000
Did the Qing Dynasty Law

42:36.000 --> 42:38.000
apply in Xinjiang?

42:38.000 --> 42:40.000
In fact, it did not.

42:40.000 --> 42:42.000
Although the Qing Dynasty Law

42:42.000 --> 42:44.000
applied to most empires,

42:44.000 --> 42:46.000
the Roman Empire

42:46.000 --> 42:48.000
also applied the law to the Jews.

42:48.000 --> 42:50.000
In the Qing Dynasty,

42:50.000 --> 42:52.000
the Mongols still applied

42:52.000 --> 42:54.000
the traditional Mongolian law,

42:54.000 --> 42:56.000
while the Tibetans still applied the Tibetan law.

42:56.000 --> 42:58.000
Only the Han people

42:58.000 --> 43:00.000
applied the Qing Dynasty Law.

43:00.000 --> 43:02.000
This is understandable.

43:02.000 --> 43:04.000
When a country is very large

43:04.000 --> 43:06.000
and is an empire,

43:06.000 --> 43:08.000
how could it be possible

43:08.000 --> 43:10.000
to force a Mongolian

43:10.000 --> 43:12.000
to marry in a Confucian way?

43:14.000 --> 43:16.000
This is also a question of

43:16.000 --> 43:18.000
the cost of rule.

43:18.000 --> 43:20.000
In order to maintain the operation of an empire

43:20.000 --> 43:22.000
and the coordination of the ethnic groups,

43:22.000 --> 43:24.000
you must use different laws

43:24.000 --> 43:26.000
to treat different people.

43:26.000 --> 43:28.000
This is now called

43:28.000 --> 43:30.000
the law pluralism.

43:30.000 --> 43:32.000
Does Taiwan want to do the same thing?

43:32.000 --> 43:34.000
Should the indigenous people

43:34.000 --> 43:36.000
apply the indigenous law

43:36.000 --> 43:38.000
or not?

43:38.000 --> 43:40.000
From the perspective of China,

43:40.000 --> 43:42.000
in 1842,

43:42.000 --> 43:44.000
the British said

43:44.000 --> 43:46.000
that they wanted to

43:46.000 --> 43:48.000
apply the British law in China.

43:48.000 --> 43:50.000
Think about it.

43:50.000 --> 43:52.000
What's wrong with

43:52.000 --> 43:54.000
the Mongolians

43:54.000 --> 43:56.000
applying the Mongolian law

43:56.000 --> 43:58.000
and the British applying the British law?

43:58.000 --> 44:00.000
At that time,

44:00.000 --> 44:02.000
foreigners could only

44:02.000 --> 44:04.000
move around

44:04.000 --> 44:06.000
when they came to China.

44:06.000 --> 44:08.000
Basically,

44:08.000 --> 44:10.000
it did not affect the original life of the Han people.

44:10.000 --> 44:12.000
Therefore,

44:12.000 --> 44:14.000
there is nothing wrong with

44:14.000 --> 44:16.000
giving you a piece of land

44:16.000 --> 44:18.000
and having your own law.

44:18.000 --> 44:20.000
In 1842,

44:20.000 --> 44:22.000
foreigners were limited to Guangzhou.

44:22.000 --> 44:24.000
We call it the Guangzhou system.

44:24.000 --> 44:26.000
Originally in Guangzhou,

44:26.000 --> 44:28.000
in 1842,

44:28.000 --> 44:30.000
China had already admitted

44:30.000 --> 44:32.000
that the Americans could apply the British law

44:32.000 --> 44:34.000
in Guangzhou.

44:34.000 --> 44:36.000
Therefore, in 1842 and 1844,

44:36.000 --> 44:38.000
foreigners came to China

44:38.000 --> 44:40.000
and told the negotiators

44:40.000 --> 44:42.000
that they wanted to apply the foreign law.

44:42.000 --> 44:44.000
The Chinese thought it was good,

44:44.000 --> 44:46.000
so they gave it to them.

44:46.000 --> 44:48.000
However, in 1868,

44:48.000 --> 44:50.000
people found that something was wrong.

44:50.000 --> 44:52.000
At first,

44:52.000 --> 44:54.000
there were many cases

44:54.000 --> 44:56.000
in which

44:56.000 --> 44:58.000
foreigners committed crimes

44:58.000 --> 45:00.000
in China

45:00.000 --> 45:02.000
and could not be punished.

45:02.000 --> 45:04.000
In these cases,

45:04.000 --> 45:06.000
too many countries had foreign law,

45:06.000 --> 45:08.000
so the legal vacuum was created.

45:08.000 --> 45:10.000
Finally,

45:10.000 --> 45:12.000
in 1910,

45:12.000 --> 45:14.000
there were 23 countries with foreign law in China.

45:14.000 --> 45:16.000
We often see in the files

45:16.000 --> 45:18.000
that an American

45:18.000 --> 45:20.000
committed a crime

45:20.000 --> 45:22.000
and was arrested in the U.S. Court.

45:22.000 --> 45:24.000
The first defense he made was

45:24.000 --> 45:26.000
that he was not an American,

45:26.000 --> 45:28.000
but an Englishman.

45:28.000 --> 45:30.000
Because he had a lot of passports,

45:30.000 --> 45:32.000
he kept hiding.

45:32.000 --> 45:34.000
Later, he made Shanghai the most

45:34.000 --> 45:36.000
famous criminal heaven in the world,

45:36.000 --> 45:38.000
because everyone would not be arrested.

45:38.000 --> 45:40.000
This problem became more and more serious,

45:40.000 --> 45:42.000
affecting China's security,

45:42.000 --> 45:44.000
China's economic development,

45:44.000 --> 45:46.000
and so on.

45:46.000 --> 45:48.000
Later,

45:48.000 --> 45:50.000
he began to think that

45:50.000 --> 45:52.000
it was a matter of right to enter the country,

45:52.000 --> 45:54.000
and we had to oppose it.

45:54.000 --> 45:56.000
To this day,

45:56.000 --> 45:58.000
there is a modern meaning.

45:58.000 --> 46:00.000
For example,

46:00.000 --> 46:02.000
every year on January 11th,

46:02.000 --> 46:04.000
there is a Judiciary Day,

46:04.000 --> 46:06.000
and the Judiciary Council

46:06.000 --> 46:08.000
holds a seminar and a celebration.

46:08.000 --> 46:10.000
Why is there a Judiciary Day

46:10.000 --> 46:12.000
on January 11th?

46:12.000 --> 46:14.000
Because January 11th, 1943

46:14.000 --> 46:16.000
was the day

46:16.000 --> 46:18.000
when China and the U.S.

46:18.000 --> 46:20.000
signed an equal treaty

46:20.000 --> 46:22.000
and abolished foreign law.

46:22.000 --> 46:24.000
They thought that from that day on,

46:24.000 --> 46:26.000
the judicial system of the Republic of China

46:26.000 --> 46:28.000
would no longer be dominated by the West.

46:28.000 --> 46:30.000
Since then,

46:30.000 --> 46:32.000
the Nationalist government

46:32.000 --> 46:34.000
moved to Taiwan in 1949,

46:34.000 --> 46:36.000
so the Judiciary Day

46:36.000 --> 46:38.000
is still on January 11th.

46:38.000 --> 46:40.000
Do you still remember

46:40.000 --> 46:42.000
the Lincoln case?

46:42.000 --> 46:44.000
It was about a British man

46:44.000 --> 46:46.000
who died in Taiwan.

46:46.000 --> 46:48.000
Later, he fled the country

46:48.000 --> 46:50.000
and returned to the U.K.

46:50.000 --> 46:52.000
At that time,

46:52.000 --> 46:54.000
the U.K. House of Representatives

46:54.000 --> 46:56.000
decided that Lincoln

46:56.000 --> 46:58.000
should be transferred back to Taiwan.

46:58.000 --> 47:00.000
The representative of the U.K.

47:00.000 --> 47:02.000
was Ambassador St. Luke.

47:02.000 --> 47:04.000
I attended his class with Ian.

47:04.000 --> 47:06.000
Ambassador St. Luke was

47:06.000 --> 47:08.000
the Minister of Foreign Affairs

47:08.000 --> 47:10.000
when he was the Minister of Foreign Affairs

47:10.000 --> 47:12.000
at the University of Taitung.

47:12.000 --> 47:14.000
He said in a newspaper

47:14.000 --> 47:16.000
that Lincoln should have

47:16.000 --> 47:18.000
a symbolic meaning,

47:18.000 --> 47:20.000
because the law in the U.K.

47:20.000 --> 47:22.000
cannot be transferred

47:22.000 --> 47:24.000
to a country that is not civilized by the law.

47:24.000 --> 47:26.000
At that time,

47:26.000 --> 47:28.000
Ambassador St. Luke wrote an article

47:28.000 --> 47:30.000
that the Lincoln case proved

47:30.000 --> 47:32.000
that the U.K. had become

47:32.000 --> 47:34.000
a country that was civilized by the law,

47:34.000 --> 47:36.000
so the U.K. would be willing

47:36.000 --> 47:38.000
to transfer people back to Taiwan.

47:38.000 --> 47:40.000
However, when the second trial was overturned,

47:40.000 --> 47:42.000
the U.K. was defeated.

47:42.000 --> 47:44.000
However, in the hearts of many

47:44.000 --> 47:46.000
lawyers and diplomats,

47:46.000 --> 47:48.000
the rule of law

47:48.000 --> 47:50.000
in the U.K.

47:50.000 --> 47:52.000
must be carried on

47:52.000 --> 47:54.000
by a civilized country.

47:54.000 --> 47:56.000
My question is very simple.

47:56.000 --> 47:58.000
Is foreign law really better?

47:58.000 --> 48:00.000
We can see that

48:00.000 --> 48:02.000
the U.S.

