I'd like to ask...

49:16.000 --> 49:18.000
When you talk about

49:18.000 --> 49:20.000
foreign law,

49:20.000 --> 49:22.000
do you mean

49:22.000 --> 49:24.000
foreign law and

49:24.000 --> 49:26.000
multilateralism?

49:26.000 --> 49:28.000
Are they the same?

49:28.000 --> 49:30.000
At least on the surface,

49:30.000 --> 49:32.000
when you talk about

49:32.000 --> 49:34.000
multilateralism,

49:34.000 --> 49:36.000
you're talking about

49:36.000 --> 49:38.000
the international community.

49:38.000 --> 49:40.000
But foreign law is about

49:40.000 --> 49:42.000
the relationship between

49:42.000 --> 49:44.000
countries.

49:44.000 --> 49:46.000
This can also be applied to...

49:46.000 --> 49:48.000
For example, you just mentioned

49:48.000 --> 49:50.000
that before 1868,

49:50.000 --> 49:52.000
China did not oppose

49:52.000 --> 49:54.000
foreign law.

49:54.000 --> 49:56.000
It is possible that

49:56.000 --> 49:58.000
they have always felt that

49:58.000 --> 50:00.000
foreign law is one form

50:00.000 --> 50:02.000
of multilateralism.

50:02.000 --> 50:04.000
After 25 years,

50:04.000 --> 50:06.000
do you think

50:06.000 --> 50:08.000
foreign law and

50:08.000 --> 50:10.000
multilateralism are related?

50:10.000 --> 50:12.000
Thank you.

50:12.000 --> 50:14.000
I think

50:14.000 --> 50:16.000
everyone can accept

50:16.000 --> 50:18.000
multilateralism

50:18.000 --> 50:20.000
under the previous rule.

50:20.000 --> 50:22.000
Because it is a low-cost

50:22.000 --> 50:24.000
way to maintain national governance.

50:24.000 --> 50:26.000
So most of the current research

50:26.000 --> 50:28.000
believes that

50:28.000 --> 50:30.000
before 1868,

50:30.000 --> 50:32.000
Chinese central government officials

50:32.000 --> 50:34.000
did not oppose

50:34.000 --> 50:36.000
multilateralism.

50:36.000 --> 50:38.000
Because it is not necessarily

50:38.000 --> 50:40.000
within a country.

50:40.000 --> 50:42.000
For example,

50:42.000 --> 50:44.000
when Western missionaries

50:44.000 --> 50:46.000
came to China,

50:46.000 --> 50:48.000
China also respected

50:48.000 --> 50:50.000
the use of its own laws

50:50.000 --> 50:52.000
to deal with its own problems.

50:52.000 --> 50:54.000
After 1868,

50:54.000 --> 50:56.000
I think it is because

50:56.000 --> 50:58.000
China wants to modernize.

50:58.000 --> 51:00.000
So in the process of modernization,

51:00.000 --> 51:02.000
we can achieve the ability

51:02.000 --> 51:04.000
of central power and mobilization

51:04.000 --> 51:06.000
that modern countries want.

51:06.000 --> 51:08.000
We can also see that

51:08.000 --> 51:10.000
after the establishment of the Republic of China,

51:10.000 --> 51:12.000
China hopes that

51:12.000 --> 51:14.000
Tibet, Mongolia and Xinjiang

51:14.000 --> 51:16.000
all use the laws of the Republic of China.

51:16.000 --> 51:18.000
China no longer respects

51:18.000 --> 51:20.000
China's autonomy.

51:20.000 --> 51:22.000
China's autonomy has become very limited.

51:22.000 --> 51:24.000
The current People's Republic of China

51:24.000 --> 51:26.000
also hopes that

51:26.000 --> 51:28.000
Mongolia, Tibet and Xinjiang

51:28.000 --> 51:30.000
all use the laws of the Republic of China.

51:30.000 --> 51:32.000
I think the same is true for Hong Kong.

51:32.000 --> 51:34.000
At the beginning,

51:34.000 --> 51:36.000
China thought that

51:36.000 --> 51:38.000
Hong Kongers could continue

51:38.000 --> 51:40.000
to use the law of the Republic of China.

51:40.000 --> 51:42.000
However, when China wants to

51:42.000 --> 51:44.000
modernize Hong Kong,

51:44.000 --> 51:46.000
it wants to adopt

51:46.000 --> 51:48.000
a new law of monolateralism.

51:48.000 --> 51:50.000
After all, we are one nation,

51:50.000 --> 51:52.000
one country.

51:52.000 --> 51:54.000
Why can't we all

51:54.000 --> 51:56.000
use different laws?

51:56.000 --> 51:58.000
If you are a Mongolian,

51:58.000 --> 52:00.000
a Tibetan, a Xinjiang or a Hong Konger,

52:00.000 --> 52:02.000
you should adopt the same law.

52:02.000 --> 52:04.000
You are not different.

52:04.000 --> 52:06.000
If you are different,

52:06.000 --> 52:08.000
you are admitting that

52:08.000 --> 52:10.000
China is not a monolateral country.

52:10.000 --> 52:12.000
I think the real difference

52:12.000 --> 52:14.000
between legal pluralism and

52:14.000 --> 52:16.000
legal monolateralism is that

52:16.000 --> 52:18.000
in the process of

52:18.000 --> 52:20.000
transferring from the empire

52:20.000 --> 52:22.000
to a democratic country,

52:22.000 --> 52:24.000
China wants to strengthen

52:24.000 --> 52:26.000
Hong Kong.

52:26.000 --> 52:28.000
In your opinion,

52:28.000 --> 52:30.000
in a democratic country,

52:30.000 --> 52:32.000
legal pluralism is

52:32.000 --> 52:34.000
different from

52:34.000 --> 52:36.000
legal monolateralism,

52:36.000 --> 52:38.000
isn't it?

52:38.000 --> 52:40.000
Not necessarily.

52:40.000 --> 52:42.000
It should be said that

52:42.000 --> 52:44.000
legal pluralism is

52:44.000 --> 52:46.000
different from

52:46.000 --> 52:48.000
legal monolateralism.

52:48.000 --> 52:50.000
It should be said that

52:50.000 --> 52:52.000
in a democratic country,

52:52.000 --> 52:54.000
you should adopt the same law.

52:54.000 --> 52:56.000
Foreigners adopt the same law

52:56.000 --> 52:58.000
because they want to

52:58.000 --> 53:00.000
show their national sovereignty.

53:00.000 --> 53:02.000
Yes.

53:02.000 --> 53:04.000
Your defense of

53:04.000 --> 53:06.000
legal pluralism is that

53:06.000 --> 53:08.000
it may show

53:08.000 --> 53:10.000
the spirit of

53:10.000 --> 53:12.000
legal pluralism.

53:12.000 --> 53:14.000
But in some countries,

53:14.000 --> 53:16.000
legal pluralism and

53:16.000 --> 53:18.000
legal monolateralism are

53:18.000 --> 53:20.000
fundamentally different.

53:20.000 --> 53:22.000
First of all,

53:22.000 --> 53:24.000
legal pluralism can,

53:24.000 --> 53:26.000
but legal monolateralism can't.

53:26.000 --> 53:28.000
Second, it can explain

53:28.000 --> 53:30.000
why China did not oppose

53:30.000 --> 53:32.000
